nd spoon. The shaggy dog sits in the foreground near the lumber. Everyone appears relaxed and cheerful, eating Cheerios amid the construction materials.\n\nThe product is then displayed prominently outdoors: a large yellow Cheerios box stands on a table with breakfast items around it. The front of the box reads “General Mills” at the top, a blue diagonal banner says “IMPROVED TOASTED OAT TASTE,” and the large black brand name “Cheerios” dominates the center. Beneath it, smaller text reads “TOASTED OAT CEREAL,” with a pictured bowl full of Cheerios and strawberries. A red circle on the upper right again reads “ONLY 1 GRAM OF SUGAR PER SERVING.” Nearby are a bowl of Cheerios, strawberries, milk, orange juice, and toast, arranged like a breakfast setting against the green yard background.\n\nA plain beige title card fills the screen with large black text reading “Cheerios,” and below it, smaller black text reads “low in sugar.”\n\nThe adult woman returns, again holding the glass bowl of Cheerios in front of the unfinished wooden structure. She smiles and speaks while holding the spoon above the bowl. Her red plaid overshirt and yellow top are clearly visible. She then pinches or picks up a piece of cereal with her fingers and brings it to her mouth, eating it with a satisfied expression.\n\nThe final title card shows large black “Cheerios” text on a beige background. Smaller black words appear underneath and expand into the phrase “number one!” so the full message reads “Cheerios number one!” As the words remain on screen, a red wheelbarrow rolls in from the right edge carrying the shaggy dog and a child in overalls, adding a playful family-yard image beside the bold product message.",
